				<B>Document List: <A HREF="/modules.php?op=modload&amp;name=Documents&amp;file=index&id=31" style="text-decoration: none;">.:: Code of Conduct ::.</A>&nbsp;
<A HREF="/modules.php?op=modload&amp;name=Documents&amp;file=index&id=28" style="text-decoration: none;">.:: Loot Guidelines ::.</A>&nbsp;
<A HREF="/modules.php?op=modload&amp;name=Documents&amp;file=index&id=29" style="text-decoration: none;">.:: Raid Procedures ::.</A>&nbsp;
<br>
</B>
				<table border="0" bgcolor="gray" 
				width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr>
				<td style="color: ivory; padding: 4px" colspan="2">
				<span STYLE="font-size: 11pt; font-weight: bold;">&nbsp;&nbsp;Guild Charter</span>
				</td></tr>
				<tr>
					<td align="left" bgcolor="white" style="font-size: 8pt">
					<A HREF="/modules.php?op=modload&amp;name=Documents&amp;file=index&id=8" style="text-decoration: none; font-size: x-small;">[contents]</A>
					</td>
					<td align="right" bgcolor="white" style="font-size: 8pt">
					<a href="javascript:history.go(-1)" style="text-decoration: none; font-size: x-small;">[back]</a>
					&nbsp;
					<A HREF="/modules.php?op=modload&amp;name=Documents&amp;file=index&loc=24&id=8" style="text-decoration: none; font-size: x-small;">&lt;&lt;&nbsp;[Guild Website Guidelines]</A>

					&nbsp;
					<A HREF="/modules.php?op=modload&amp;name=Documents&amp;file=index&loc=26&id=8" style="text-decoration: none; font-size: x-small;">[Unruly Player Guidelines]&nbsp;&gt;&gt;</A>

					</td>
				</tr>
				</table><H3>Miscellany</H3>
<b><u>Conflict Resolution</u></b><br>
<br>
In the event that there are disagreements between some of our members, we expect you to behave maturely and work things out as adults. If it becomes a detriment to the guild morale or becomes a problem for other members an officer will step in to see that things are settled. Please respect other people's rights and playing styles, even if you disagree with them.<br>
<br>
Players who have issues or concerns of any kind should send officers a tell or email as soon as they feel they have a problem. Don't let something spiral out of control; your officers are here to help you. If you have any problems get them out into the open.<br>
<br>
<u><b>Disciplinary Actions</b></u><br>
<br>
Be aware that the officers are required to listen to information about you from other players that are not in our guild. If you do something to cause trouble for others our officers are required to take disciplinary action as they see fit once they understand the entirety of the situation. We'll take most non-guild complaints with a grain of salt but if you begin to develop a history of problems we may have to do something about it.<br>
<br>
The removal of any player from the guild can be accomplished by any officer at any time. Shortly afterwards, the officers will have a meeting to discuss the events leading to the player's removal. If the original officer's decision is upheld, the player will remain removed. If the original officer's decision is overturned, the player will be invited back. The officer will be reprimanded and may lose his status as an officer if his decision wasn't merited.<br>
<br>
<b><u>Power Leveling</u></b><br>
<br>
Power Leveling is when you have a higher-level player assist another lower-level player in killing creatures for fast experience. Power Leveling is not recommended for a number of reasons. It tends to grow a player's abilities far faster than the player's skill to operate their character in game. Everquest teaches many lessons during the leveling grind that are absolutely essential to higher-level play. Also, your characters skills are the main force behind how effective he is and when power leveling the skills often lag behind what they should be, leaving you at a higher level with inferior skills, thus making you a liability to your group.<br>
<br>
We do not offer power-leveling services as a guild to any members. We will not power level you through several levels in one day. We may, at the discretion of the higher-level player, assist you in breaking through a hell level quickly, or advancing a few levels quickly for a skilled player starting a new class of character.<br>
<br>
There are some times when these rules will be bent or broken, and we may power level certain characters intensely to get them to higher levels. This will happen very rarely if at all, and it is at the discretion of the Officers of the guild. We had to do this once when we were a lower-level guild and needed higher-level enchanters and clerics to be effective on raids. It has not happened since.<br>
<br>
<b><u>Guild Armory & Treasury</u></b><br>
<br>
The Guild Armory is comprised of good bits of equipment that have been generously donated by guild members. All of the items in this armory are the property of the guild. The guild officers maintain ownership of these items, usually stored on alternate characters. The purpose of the armory is to outfit our members with items that they can use to level themselves quickly and help others out by making them more effective. The officers maintain a list of the items in the armory and to whom the item is currently assigned. Officers decide who gets to use these items and for how long they may keep them.<br>
<br>
We assign the items to specific characters based on our own assessment of need. If you receive an item in this way from the guild, do not sell it or trade it away without the express permission of the officer who assigned the item to you. You are allowed to keep the item until it is needed for another person or until you find a better replacement for it yourself. Once you are done with the item return it to an officer.<br>
<br>
The Guild Treasury is simply a large bank account on one of the officer's alternate characters for storing money that belongs to the guild. This money is used to defray the costs of plane raids, purchase new items for the Armory, and for guild raffles. The majority of this cash comes from donations, plane raids, and other guild events. This money is only used to benefit the guild. All accounting for it is handled by the council of elders.<br>
<br>
<b><u>Velious Faction</b></u><br>
We have chosen to side with the Coldain (dwarves) and the Claws of Veeshan (dragons), and go against the Kromzek (giants). The reasons for this are simple. We lack the firepower as a guild raid the places where the quest items for the giants drop. We can however raid the places the Coldain quest items can be obtained with little trouble. Also, being on good dragon faction makes it much easier to travel safely around velious, as many of the deeper zones (Cobalt Scar, Western Wastes) have a large number of critters that are on the dragon faction, giving us relatively safe passage through those areas. The giants do have the best quest armors, however the dragon quest armors are equally difficult to obtain and are so close in stats that the difference hardly matters. Being on good dragon faction, if we ever do get the firepower, means we can do those quests if we choose. There are also a large number of non-armor quests in Skyshrine that give great rewards, so we aren't shorting ourselves on quests by doing things this way. You can bind safely in Thurgadin, as well as buy, sell, and bank there. Basically, this means avoid killing any dwarves and dragons, but feel free to kill as many giants as you like. Once you have good dragon faction, you will be able to use the druid rings in the wakening lands since Wuoshi (the resident dragon) will leave you alone.<br>
<br>
When you start off in Velious, you'll be apprehensive or indifferent to the Coldain, and KoS to the Kromzek and Claws of Veeshan. One day of killing giants should make you Warmly to the Coldain. It will take a lot of hunting giants inside Kael Drakkel (the giant city) to make you non-KoS to the dragons. Once you are no longer KoS, there are a number of simple quests you can do to further boost your dragon faction without killing more giants.<br>
<br>
The way the factions are set up, it's not possible to be on good terms with all three faction sets. You can maintain good faction with Coldain and Claws at the same time, but for any other arrangement you will be KoS to two of the three factions. Siding with giants means you will be KoS to the dwarves and dragons.<br>
